WEBVTT

00:02.078 --> 00:03.977
Cumulostratus cloud cover moving in.

00:04.046 --> 00:07.081
Barometric readings
indicate a rising tropopause.

00:07.150 --> 00:08.617
In anticipation of a visit

00:08.617 --> 00:11.445
from the president of the
Royal Meteorological Society,

00:11.488 --> 00:14.222
I have completed construction
on a state-of-the-art instrument

00:14.291 --> 00:17.259
that will harness the
energy of the weather itself.

00:17.327 --> 00:20.495
I am just so excited to be inducted

00:20.564 --> 00:23.331
as an official Thunder Queen of the RMS.

00:23.400 --> 00:26.668
Oh, uh, only lead researchers
on a project get inducted.

00:26.737 --> 00:28.503
I'm going to be inducted?

00:28.572 --> 00:29.880
No, I am!

00:30.074 --> 00:31.640
This is my experiment.

00:31.709 --> 00:34.376
Abortion Deb, you did
draw up the schematics.

00:34.445 --> 00:36.812
I designed the equipment
and did all the math.

00:36.880 --> 00:39.781
And I paid the $6 application fee.

00:39.850 --> 00:42.417
Which is why I will be
supervising the event

00:42.486 --> 00:44.419
from a safe distance,
preparing for my new title...

00:44.488 --> 00:45.987
A scheming bitch?

00:46.056 --> 00:48.256
Conduct the experiment yourself

00:48.325 --> 00:50.792
since you're the lead researcher.

00:50.861 --> 00:52.294
- Hmpf!
- Abortion Deb, Cornetta?

00:52.362 --> 00:53.528
Girls? Come back!

00:53.597 --> 00:55.197
I can't do this without you!

00:56.266 --> 00:57.866
Who will hold my poles?

00:57.935 --> 00:59.568
Are you almost done with this room?

00:59.636 --> 01:01.656
Mayor Cutie wants to take a shit in here.

01:02.272 --> 01:03.638
Sisters.

01:03.707 --> 01:06.241
I have a rare opportunity for you.

01:06.310 --> 01:08.243
Ooh! Invitations to your second funeral?

01:10.637 --> 01:13.271
Imagine the chance to
participate in an experiment

01:13.296 --> 01:16.561
that will change forever the way we look at

01:16.905 --> 01:17.977
weather.

01:17.978 --> 01:20.612
Hortense, apart from the
civil rights of poor people,

01:20.680 --> 01:22.313
there's nothing more
boring than the weather.

01:22.338 --> 01:23.258
Ugh.

01:23.302 --> 01:25.014
I certainly hope you're joking.

01:27.768 --> 01:28.934
For the weather...

01:29.975 --> 01:31.274
Is my life.

01:31.334 --> 01:33.849
I am Juan Pablo El Castillo,

01:34.178 --> 01:36.749
and I have come all the way from Barcelona

01:37.047 --> 01:38.457
to meet Hortense.

01:39.183 --> 01:40.446
And to make love...

01:41.218 --> 01:42.334
to her mind.

01:43.819 --> 01:44.953
Hello, Doctor.

01:45.022 --> 01:46.119
I love the weather!

01:46.144 --> 01:47.256
Me too!

01:47.324 --> 01:48.490
Except for rain.

01:48.559 --> 01:49.725
And snow.

01:49.793 --> 01:50.893
And gentle breezes.

01:50.961 --> 01:52.060
Yes, uh,

01:52.129 --> 01:53.395
we like our breezes rough.

01:53.464 --> 01:54.967
- Mm-hmm.
- Hmm.

