towered to your liking?

02:20.832 --> 02:23.232
We could add a spire of plum butter

02:23.301 --> 02:24.900
to the summit if you prefer.

02:24.969 --> 02:27.058
No, it's not the pillars.

02:27.605 --> 02:30.506
It's just that life has become less sunny

02:30.575 --> 02:32.508
since I've discontinued my morphine use.

02:32.577 --> 02:34.510
My God, Madam, I'll
inject you straight away.

02:34.579 --> 02:35.892
No, Peepers.

02:36.202 --> 02:38.848
I think not being on morphine
is ultimately better for me

02:38.916 --> 02:40.516
than being on morphine.

02:40.585 --> 02:42.151
Well, I'm not a doctor,
but that sounds like

02:42.220 --> 02:43.719
a load of piffle.

02:43.788 --> 02:47.707
I need something to invigorate the spirit.

02:48.092 --> 02:50.659
Some adventure.

02:50.728 --> 02:53.062
Perhaps something involving
the great outdoors.

02:53.130 --> 02:54.463
Oh, no, Madam.

02:54.532 --> 02:56.465
At your age, even the lesser outdoors

02:56.534 --> 02:57.844
could kill you.

03:01.801 --> 03:03.340
I have an idea.

03:04.008 --> 03:05.828
A pleasure cruise.

03:06.191 --> 03:07.943
Well, if I can't get high,

03:08.012 --> 03:10.145
at least I can get on the high seas!

03:14.886 --> 03:16.752
I'm sure you get this all the time,

03:16.821 --> 03:18.921
but what is rain?

03:18.990 --> 03:21.056
When water condenses in the atmosphere...

03:21.125 --> 03:22.758
What language are you speaking?

03:22.827 --> 03:24.426
I can't believe it's finally happening.

03:24.495 --> 03:26.428
Sex with a Spanish male has been atop both

03:26.497 --> 03:28.097
of our bucket lists for years.

03:28.165 --> 03:30.099
It's the only thing our
lists have in common.

03:30.167 --> 03:31.767
Mine mostly involves technology

03:31.836 --> 03:32.935
that hasn't been invented yet,

03:33.004 --> 03:34.774
like a mechanical Beatrice.

03:34.906 --> 03:36.772
Mine is to figure out what a bucket is.

03:37.902 --> 03:40.069
The goal of my experiment

03:40.344 --> 03:42.978
is to attract lightning,

03:43.047 --> 03:46.482
and then use the energy
as a controlled force.

03:46.550 --> 03:48.484
At least there's something
out there we can control.

03:48.552 --> 03:49.558
Ladies.

03:49.669 --> 03:51.703
A storm is like a bull...

03:51.772 --> 03:53.705
wild and unpredictable.

03:54.181 --> 03:55.355
But like a bull,

03:55.515 --> 03:56.640
it can be tamed.

03:56.640 --> 03:58.246
Oh, you can tame me if you pull my hair.

03:58.271 --> 03:59.473
Me too!

03:59.543 --> 04:00.976
Also, it helps if you call me chambermaid

04:01.044 --> 04:02.177
while you pull.

04:02.513 --> 04:03.479
This part's fake.

04:03.548 --> 04:05.481
Yes, and Juan Pablo,

04:05.550 --> 04:07.146
as every matador knows,

04:07.146 --> 04:10.478
to truly dominate the
bull, one must be safe.

04:10.503 --> 04:12.070
That is completely wrong.

04:12.138 --> 04:14.072
- What?
- You must be a risk taker.

04:14.140 --> 04:15.940
Yes, well, no disrespect,
but what do you know

04:16.009 --> 04:17.766
- about bullfighting?
- I'm Spanish.

04:18.345 --> 04:20.002
And a professional bullfighter.

04:20.613 --> 04:21.946
And I published a book called

04:22.015 --> 04:23.748
"How the Weather Is Like a Bull."

04:25.051 --> 04:26.980
It sold 1 million copies.

04:27.187 --> 04:28.753
Yes, well, off to the woods.

04:28.822 --> 04:30.054
Let's just hope no one gets killed.

04:34.694 --> 04:36.471
<i>I've never been so excited.</i>

04:36.696 --> 04:38.563
Lady Dodo and myself,

04:38.632 --> 04:40.846
all alone for a whole day.

04:42.135 --> 04:43.935
Well, Lady Dodo, myself, and the captain.

04:44.971 --> 04:46.118
And the deckhands.

04:46.143 --> 04:47.671
<i>And the chef.</i>

04:47.807 --> 04:49.447
<i>And the other guests,
and their staffs.</i>

04:49.560 --> 04:50.685
The orchestra,

04:50.685 --> 04:52.952
and the electro-technical
officer, and the boatswain,

04:53.021 --> 04:55.588
and the able seamen,
and the ordinary seamen.

04:55.906 --> 04:56.905
<i>But other than that...</i>

04:58.442 --> 04:59.508
Alone.

05:00.811 --> 05:02.244
This is your cabin, Madam.

05:05.449 --> 05:08.416
One canopy bed, Captain?

05:08.485 --> 05:11.586
I suppose I'll be sleeping
where I nap like a commoner.

05:11.874 --> 05:14.942
And through here are quarters for your man.

05:17.052 --> 05:18.627
My own cot?

05:18.794 --> 05:21.629
Is this a pleasure cruise,
or a paradise cruise?

05:21.697 --> 05:23.330
Now, sir, if you must pass water,

05:23.399 --> 05:25.399
you may do so over the side of the ship.

05:25.468 --> 05:27.401
If you have to defecate, you must hold it.

05:27.470 --> 05:29.071
My good man, I always hold it.

05:30.337 --> 05:33.107
The fresh air, the open sea.

05:33.175 --> 05:36.110
We're really roughing it now, Peepers!

05:36.178 --> 05:38.612
Not I, Madam. I fear I may grow spoiled

05:38.681 --> 05:40.714
with these lavish accommodations.

05:55.703 --> 05:57.510
Where is your rain gear?

05:57.535 --> 05:59.835
- This is my rain gear.
- I'm not wearing rain gear.

05:59.904 --> 06:01.570
- I'm trying to [BLEEP].
- I need you focused!

06:01.639 --> 06:04.807
These two rods will harness
the energy of the lightning.

06:04.876 --> 06:07.324
If they are not firmly in the ground,

06:07.324 --> 06:09.424
someone could be electrocuted.

06:09.774 --> 06:12.522
Now hold your poles in place,
and don't screw this up!

06:13.378 --> 06:15.445
Biblioteca Gracias is mine.

06:15.513 --> 06:16.646
He's hot-blooded.

06:16.714 --> 06:18.514
He's not interested in your anemic beauty.

06:18.582 --> 06:20.285
- Can't we both have him?
- Of course not!

06:20.332 --> 06:21.593
Here's how it goes.

06:21.593 --> 06:23.426
I say what I want, and you
acquiesce to my demands.

06:23.495 --> 06:25.028
He's mine, say it!

06:25.096 --> 06:26.429
- He's mine!
- He's mine!

06:26.498 --> 06:27.597
He's mine!

06:27.666 --> 06:29.014
He's mine!

06:30.836 --> 06:31.968
Ow!

06:39.244 --> 06:40.743
He's on my bucket list!

06:40.812 --> 06:42.245
My bucket list!

06:47.018 --> 06:48.218
No, no, no, no!

06:48.286 --> 06:50.086
Don't cross the lightning rods!

06:50.155 --> 06:51.621
Are you insane?

06:51.690 --> 06:52.922
You'll both be electrocuted.

06:52.991 --> 06:54.557
No! Give it!

06:54.626 --> 06:55.592
Ladies, please...

06:55.660 --> 06:57.075
Stop!

06:58.296 --> 06:59.943
Give. Me. That.

07:00.232 --> 07:01.788
Pole!

07:03.635 --> 07:04.759
Oh, my God.

07:05.670 --> 07:06.903
Oh, my God!

07:06.972 --> 07:08.235
We've killed him.

07:08.573 --> 07:11.307
And against all odds, it had
nothing to do with the weather!

07:15.442 --> 07:16.708
I think I'm...

07:16.799 --> 07:18.032
I'm actually...

07:18.057 --> 07:19.215
I'm actually okay.

07:24.089 --> 07:26.155
What does "okay" mean in English?

07:28.260 --> 07:29.525
And if we are very lucky,

07:29.594 --> 07:31.294
we may even see whales.

07:31.363 --> 07:33.800
Majestic, clever creatures, whales.

07:34.199 --> 07:36.199
With emotions and language.

07:36.268 --> 07:37.810
Complex social ties.

07:38.169 --> 07:40.670
As God as my witness, nothing feels better

07:40.739 --> 07:42.213
than killing a whale.

07:43.108 --> 07:45.041
Harpoons will be available on all decks.

07:50.615 --> 07:52.548
Sweet merciful Poseidon.

07:56.054 --> 07:57.420
A sea twister.

07:59.891 --> 08:02.292
Everyone, return to your cabins at once.

08:02.360 --> 08:03.960
What about the lifeboats?

08:04.029 --> 08:05.595
Do you have any idea what
happens to a 12-foot boat

08:05.664 --> 08:07.530
when it's crushed by a 30-foot wave?

08:07.599 --> 08:09.132
- Well, of course not.
- No one does!

08:09.157 --> 08:10.523
No one's ever lived through it.

08:10.548 --> 08:12.481
We are not long for this world.

08:12.637 --> 08:14.111
Now...

08:16.074 --> 08:17.040
Panic!

08:21.680 --> 08:23.012
We must get you to safety!

08:23.081 --> 08:24.080
- Oh.
- This way!

08:24.149 --> 08:25.515
This way, quickly.

08:25.583 --> 08:26.660
Quickly!

08:40.044 --> 08:41.998
Oh, my God! Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

08:42.067 --> 08:42.999
We killed him.

08:43.068 --> 08:44.334
My science killed him.

08:44.402 --> 08:45.601
What are we going to do?

08:45.670 --> 08:47.837
I had a story like this read to me once!

08:47.906 --> 08:49.505
It was called "Slipper Beauty,"

08:49.574 --> 08:52.008
and it says to tongue him
till he comes back to life.

08:52.077 --> 08:53.582
You don't tell me twice.

08:56.948 --> 08:57.981
Well, you must not be his true love

08:58.049 --> 08:59.482
because he's not coming back to life.

09:02.887 --> 09:04.721
- No!
- You're not doing it right!

09:04.789 --> 09:05.960
Get off!

09:09.761 --> 09:11.138
I want...

09:13.025 --> 09:15.565
No, no! Stop it! Stop it!

09:17.203 --> 09:19.270
We need a real plan!

09:21.706 --> 09:23.406
Ooh, Hortense, taking it all the way.

09:23.475 --> 09:24.640
- Impressive.
- No!

09:24.709 --> 09:27.110
I am just trying to pick him up.

09:27.178 --> 09:29.245
- But he's stiff.
- That makes two of us.

09:29.314 --> 09:31.180
What are we going to do?

09:31.249 --> 09:33.059
We'll probably go to prison for life.

09:33.385 --> 09:35.084
Of course, a rich person's
prison is better than

09:35.153 --> 09:37.320
the most extravagant
poor person's vacation,

09:37.389 --> 09:38.494
but still.

09:39.290 --> 09:40.757
We have to get rid of the body.

09:44.095 --> 09:45.709
- Oh!
- Whoa!

09:45.964 --> 09:47.230
Oh, Peepers.

09:47.986 --> 09:49.500
I don't want to die.

09:49.567 --> 09:51.134
I'm frightened.

09:51.202 --> 09:54.032
- Hold me?
- Anything for you, Lady Dodo.

09:56.307 --> 09:58.941
Hamish, we saw a gopher
in the raspberry bushes.

09:59.010 --> 10:00.127
Got it.

10:01.546 --> 10:03.479
- Where's the corpse?
- In the woods.

10:03.548 --> 10:04.614
By the servant burial heap.

10:04.682 --> 10:06.482
- Hmm.
- You've done this before?

10:06.551 --> 10:07.917
Of course. What else did you think

10:07.986 --> 10:09.218
I did around here?

10:09.287 --> 10:10.920
You've done this before?

10:10.989 --> 10:12.255
What's that now?

10:12.323 --> 10:14.857
