15:16.622 --> 15:18.255
for this body, and it's not going to be me.

15:18.324 --> 15:20.157
Surely they're going to find us out.

15:20.226 --> 15:22.026
- Should I burn my clothes?
- You know, that's probably

15:22.095 --> 15:23.761
a good idea from a fashion perspective.

15:23.830 --> 15:25.396
Your clothes look so bad
when you're wearing them.

15:25.465 --> 15:26.497
- Please do.
- Really.

15:26.566 --> 15:27.631
You just dress terribly.

15:27.700 --> 15:29.233
Burn everything now.

15:29.302 --> 15:30.968
Your face matches your little lace thing,

15:31.037 --> 15:33.204
and it feels like you kind
of, like, threw up lace,

15:33.272 --> 15:34.805
and then you just left it there,

15:34.874 --> 15:36.207
and then you're, like...

15:36.275 --> 15:37.475
All the way down, and you're, like,

15:37.543 --> 15:39.009
"This is my wardrobe forever."

15:39.078 --> 15:40.282
Commit suicide.

15:47.420 --> 15:49.587
Well, I was thinking we should probably

15:49.655 --> 15:51.188
keep our love secret at first,

15:51.257 --> 15:53.057
at least until you've told the girls,

15:53.126 --> 15:55.059
and in time, I hope they
can come to think of me

15:55.128 --> 15:56.738
as their father.

15:56.738 --> 15:58.696
As for the house, I
will continue to run it.

15:58.765 --> 16:01.565
Naturally, we'll need to
find a new butler eventually.

16:01.634 --> 16:03.734
As for the wedding, I think
we should keep it simple.

16:03.803 --> 16:05.182
Elegant, of course.

16:05.182 --> 16:07.605
I was thinking an "Arabian Nights" theme.

16:07.673 --> 16:09.807
Peepers, we need to talk.

16:09.876 --> 16:12.510
Oh, I could talk the day
away with you, my darling.

16:12.578 --> 16:15.045
People say things when
they're about to die.

16:15.114 --> 16:18.215
I'm certain you also said
things you didn't mean,

16:18.284 --> 16:22.155
and I think maybe it's best
if we just kept things casual.

16:24.357 --> 16:25.589
Casual?

16:25.658 --> 16:26.824
Yes!

16:26.893 --> 16:28.759
- Yes, of course!
- Ah.

16:28.828 --> 16:30.261
Casual.

16:30.329 --> 16:32.897
What is a butler, if not casual?

16:32.965 --> 16:33.931
Think of it,

16:33.931 --> 16:35.864
a butler marrying his mistress.

16:35.932 --> 16:37.098
- Absurd.
- Ooh!

16:44.657 --> 16:46.219
I'm back.

16:46.289 --> 16:49.189
How are my angels and Hortense?

16:54.397 --> 16:55.470
Mother!

16:55.698 --> 16:57.198
You'll never guess what happened.

16:57.198 --> 16:59.533
I killed a man with a lead
pipe, and then we slept together.

16:59.602 --> 17:01.435
We've got the confession right here.

17:01.504 --> 17:02.870
- I can't...
- Shh, shh.

17:02.939 --> 17:04.665
Frederick, did you kill anybody?

17:05.174 --> 17:08.142
- No.
- I need to know the truth.

17:08.166 --> 17:09.633
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

17:09.944 --> 17:11.233
I didn't do it.

17:11.233 --> 17:13.953
Well, then why did you
say all of the things?

17:13.992 --> 17:15.674
How did you come up with it?

17:16.395 --> 17:18.878
- Guessing.
- What do you mean guessing?

17:19.510 --> 17:20.740
I guessed.

17:20.740 --> 17:23.279
Frederick, that's not
something to guess about.

17:23.279 --> 17:24.342
<i>Buenos días.</i>

17:26.261 --> 17:27.363
Am I wet here?

17:27.387 --> 17:28.737
I'm wet here.

17:29.810 --> 17:31.543
Did no one check his pulse?

17:31.611 --> 17:32.977
No, I did.

17:33.046 --> 17:34.979
I told his heart beat once for alive,

17:35.048 --> 17:36.977
and twice for dead, and it did twice.

17:38.169 --> 17:39.769
Wait, now I'm confused.

17:39.837 --> 17:41.003
Did I kill him or not?

17:42.974 --> 17:44.073
Someone tell me!

17:49.061 --> 17:50.690
Oh, how was the cruise?

17:50.741 --> 17:52.074
Wonderful. Thank you, Garfield.

17:52.142 --> 17:53.805
Oh, that's good.

17:56.846 --> 17:57.937
Actually,

17:58.415 --> 17:59.781
it wasn't wonderful.

17:59.849 --> 18:00.930
Oh?

18:01.718 --> 18:02.997
I met a lady.

18:03.520 --> 18:05.419
Oh, what a lady.

18:05.755 --> 18:07.387
I grew enamored with her.

18:07.591 --> 18:08.801
Bewitched.

18:09.077 --> 18:11.629
And I thought she was
enamored with me, but...

18:12.098 --> 18:15.725
it turns out my feelings
for her were just mirages.

18:15.750 --> 18:16.916
What shall I do?

18:16.985 --> 18:18.150
Shall I chase after her

18:18.219 --> 18:20.215
like a hound chasing a fox,

18:20.270 --> 18:24.139
or does one have pride
and wait upon one's roost,

18:24.208 --> 18:27.075
like the cock crowing at the morn?

18:27.144 --> 18:30.812
I've never been anything
but there for her, you know?

18:30.881 --> 18:33.648
And now she just treats
me as if I am just somebody

18:33.717 --> 18:35.475
that she used to know.

18:35.572 --> 18:37.138
Somebody.

18:37.163 --> 18:38.729
Well, your problem is that you're looking

18:38.754 --> 18:41.622
for comfort and support
in the arms of a woman.

18:41.935 --> 18:44.603
That's like going to the
latrine for drinking water.

18:44.671 --> 18:48.060
It might quench your thirst,
but you'll end up with listeria.

18:48.275 --> 18:50.075
The thing to do is move on.

18:50.100 --> 18:53.101
But how do I do that,
sir, when she's right...

18:53.126 --> 18:54.459
When she's right...

18:54.575 --> 18:56.508
Oh-ho-ho!
There you are.

18:56.533 --> 18:58.299
I've been looking everywhere for you.

18:58.358 --> 18:59.987
- I'm here.
- Doctor.

19:00.454 --> 19:04.189
Prepare me something so
that I shan't feel my face.

19:04.258 --> 19:06.057
- Allow me, Madam.
- Oh. No, no, no.

19:06.126 --> 19:07.814
I don't need you, Peepers.

19:10.297 --> 19:12.230
You know, I... I'm thinking of it,

19:12.299 --> 19:14.266
and perhaps you should try a melon.

19:14.334 --> 19:16.768
You know, the simplest
relationship I ever had

19:16.837 --> 19:18.870
was with a cantaloupe named Luther.

19:22.909 --> 19:24.276
You wanted to see me, sir?

19:24.344 --> 19:25.640
Come in. Come in.

19:26.780 --> 19:27.733
Well,

19:28.474 --> 19:30.719
there's no easy way to say
this, so I'll just say it.

19:30.744 --> 19:32.110
I'm leaving Bellacourt.

19:33.713 --> 19:35.446
Another harbor cruise?

19:35.515 --> 19:36.587
No!

19:37.183 --> 19:38.302
This time,

19:38.583 --> 19:39.916
I'm leaving for good.

19:40.953 --> 19:42.119
But... but...

19:42.188 --> 19:43.353
- But why?
- Never mind why,

19:43.422 --> 19:45.122
- you impudent bug!
- Oh.

19:45.191 --> 19:47.091
You are the head butler now.

19:47.159 --> 19:48.492
No.

19:48.561 --> 19:50.894
Responsibilities of the great house

19:50.963 --> 19:52.996
have fallen upon your shoulders.

19:53.065 --> 19:56.734
May you join the top stair

19:57.503 --> 19:59.219
of the downstair life.

19:59.772 --> 20:01.505
Ah, your lapel!

20:01.574 --> 20:02.706
Yes, my lapel.

20:04.287 --> 20:08.228
I've ripped it as sign to
signify the end of my tenure here

20:08.253 --> 20:09.319
in Bellacourt.

20:09.319 --> 20:11.319
And now your tenure begins, boy.

20:11.850 --> 20:13.292
Remember what I told you.

20:13.316 --> 20:14.702
Dead eyes.

20:15.006 --> 20:17.255
Dead eye. That's it.

20:17.294 --> 20:19.279
- You're ready.
- I'm your, just...

20:20.013 --> 20:21.303
my old friend.

20:23.108 --> 20:24.232
No tears.

20:24.701 --> 20:25.990
Dead eyes.

20:25.990 --> 20:27.552
Dead eyes, dead heart.

20:28.420 --> 20:31.342
Now... there's silver to be polished.

20:31.381 --> 20:32.693
Go ahead, buttle boy.

20:32.952 --> 20:34.318
You're the head butler now.

20:34.387 --> 20:36.296
I'm the head butler now?

20:36.986 --> 20:38.519
I'm the head butler now.

20:39.105 --> 20:40.296
Dead eyes, old boy.

